news.title: Odisha government begins land settlement in favour of ST villagers in Cuttack slum
news.para: The Khurda collector has directed the district welfare officer (DWO) “to take immediate action” for settlement of the land in favour of the villagers.

news.title: Barratt to buy Redrow in 2.52 billion pound deal
news.para: The newest combination, to be named "Barratt Redrow", aims to deliver more than 22,000 homes each year in the medium term, or 57% to 63% more than the 13,500 to 14,000 deliveries Barratt expects to deliver by itself in fiscal 2024.

news.title: UK house prices gain momentum in early 2024: Halifax
news.para: Kim Kinnaird, director of mortgages at Halifax, said a recent drop in mortgage rates, falling inflation and a resilient labour market had boosted confidence among buyers and sellers in early 2024.

news.title: Suvita Real Estates plans NCD issue to raise Rs 105 crore
news.para: The bonds have step-up pricing such that the real estate company will pay investors 17.25% for 12 months and 20.25% between 13 and 15 months, stated a term-sheet circulated by the company. At the same time, the company will have the right to redeem the bonds at the end of 12 months. In the event of default, the company will pay 24% to the investors.

news.title: Why New York City apartment buildings are on sale now for 50% off
news.para: Last year, New York buildings with at least one rent-­stabilized apartment sold on average for $203,000 a unit, down 34% since 2019. One of the key reasons for drop in apartment prices in New York is tough rent control. These rules benefit longtime tenants at the expense of newcomers, and they’re an inefficient way to help those who need it most, scholars have found.

news.title: Garuda Construction and Engineering files draft papers to raise funds via IPO
news.para: The proposed IPO is a combination of a fresh issue of 1.83 crore equity shares and an Offer For Sale of 95 lakh equity shares by promoter PKH Ventures Ltd, according to the Draft Red Herring Prospectus (DRHP) uploaded on Sebi's website on Wednesday.

news.title: Delhi LG approves DDA budget of Rs 8,811 crore for 2024-25
news.para: Lieutenant Governor V K Saxena, while approving the budget, said the authority will undertake several developmental projects during the next financial year that will focus on better housing, aesthetic upgradation of the landscape and restoration and preservation of the city's heritage.

news.title: DDA approves land use changes, housing schemes to enhance public infrastructure
news.para: "Several decisions were given the go-ahead for housing schemes to boost the sector and for development of Narela sub-city. The authority approved the proposals on change of land use in public interest - in Ghazipur for setting up RFID, in Auchandi village for construction of electrical sub-station, in Jangpura for RRTS installations," the statement read.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 3,000 units for failure to pay property tax
news.para: The West Zone recorded the highest number of sealed properties at 1,686. The officials recovered pending tax amounting to Rs 5.81 crore during the sealing drive.

news.title: Punjab does away with NOC for property registration
news.para: Chief minister Bhagwant Mann said that the decision had been taken to save people from facing inconvenience. He added that the legal mechanism for the decision had already been worked out and details would be made public soon.

news.title: Stricter building rules to be implemented in Howrah
news.para: Municipal affairs department minister Firhad Hakim presented the amendment bill in the assembly on Tuesday, emphasising the need for stricter rules for building clearance to bring them in line with the KMC standards. Under the proposed amendments.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body asks UT administration to pay Rs 16 crore in property tax
news.para: The estimates have been prepared by the property tax branch of the civic body after assessing the tax amount of each department of the UT administration.

news.title: Kanpur, Meerut metro corridors to roll out by 2025
news.para: The UP Metro rail corporation and National Capital Region transport corporation plan to roll out full-fledged Metro corridors in Kanpur and Meerut by 2024-25. The Kanpur corridor will have 21 stations and cater to around 1.5 lakh commuters daily. The Meerut corridor, running along RapidX, will have 13 stations and is expected to be completed by March 2025.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP will introduce IVRS to remind property tax defaulters to settle dues
news.para: BBMP is all set to introduce an Integrated Voice Response System (IVRS), which will keep reminding the defautlers of their obligation to clear their dues. Munish Moudgil, special commissioner (revenue), confirmed to TOI that the Palike will introduce IVRS shortly to remind tax defaulters like banks that send out reminders to their customers.

news.title: Bidhannagar civic body to collect penalty & interest on property tax dues from April 1
news.para: The penalty and interest was supposed to be payable from Oct 1 last year, but the civic authorities deferred the plan. Officials said that it would be easier for the authorities to calculate and impose the penalty and fine on arrears of all the four quarters of the year instead of taking the penalty and interest for the first two quarters and then again calculating the arrears for the third and fourth quarters.

news.title: About Rs 239 crore allotted for second phase of Kochi Metro
news.para: One of the major allocations is Rs 239 crore set aside for the second phase of Kochi Metro rail. The preparatory works for the second hase from Palarivattom to Infopark at Kakkanad are on. The allocation will help fuel land acquisition and other preliminary works.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government allocates Rs 2,441 crore for PMAY-Rural
news.para: The development comes less than a week after the interim Union Budget earmarked Rs 32,000 crore for the scheme that aims to construct 2 crore more housing units in the rural areas.

news.title: Maharashtra government likely to consider relief for nazul property
news.para: Pravin Datke, BJP MLC, confirmed the development, saying the relief is being offered on three fronts. Datke said, “The major issue is that most of the lesses have breached their conditions by making alterations into the design of the house. The govt says no action will be taken against them.”

news.title: Mumbai: Sai Estate Consultant directors arrested for cheating & forgery
news.para: ​​​​​This is the third case in which Wadhwani has been arrested. Deputy commissioner of police (EOW) Sangramsingh Nishandar said that on Tuesday, the police registered an FIR at Amboli police station in Andheri and arrested Amit and Vicky under the IPC sections of cheating, forgery and criminal breach of trust.

news.title: Axis Bank leases over 81,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Vile Parle
news.para: Axis Bank has leased over 81,300 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Parle Product Factory Compound for 5 years with a monthly rent of Rs 85.37 lakh. The agreement includes a 12% rental escalation after 3 years. The lease and rent commencement dates are in 2024. Axis Bank will have exclusive access to 81 four-wheeler parking spaces and 300 two-wheeler parking slots.
